// @test regression/INV104-switch-subject-case-type
// @description A switch WITH a subject desugars each case to `subject == case`; a case value incomparable with the subject is TV's CE10123 for `operator ==` (subject `close` is series float, the case "a" is a literal string). A switch whose cases match the subject type (and a no-subject switch) stay clean. Probed 2026-06-25 via pine-lint --tv, see INV104.
// @expects parse: success
// @expects error: line=4, message=/Cannot call "operator ==" with argument "expr1"="a"/
// @expects errors: 1

//@version=6
indicator("INV104-switch-subject-case-type")
x = switch close
    "a" => 1
    => 2
i = 3
y = switch i
    1 => 10
    => 0
plot(x + y)
